<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFACFFF66DC2FA51FD11AD02" blockId="8.[178,1085,1484,1536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1521">
Diagnosis: Within 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFACFFF66CA0FA51FDFAAEE0" box="[464,623,1484,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Platynopterinae">Platynopterinae</taxonomicName>
only in members of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFACFFF66E17FA51FC71AEE3" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" box="[871,996,1484,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Ambonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFACFFF66E17FA51FC71AEE3" box="[871,996,1484,1505]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1521">Ambonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the pronotalsides strongly up-curved and flanged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
